fashion writing and the arts arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery fashion writing and the arts cathy horyn new york times fashion critic discusses fashion writing and the arts with nancy troy chair of art and art history at stanford the stanford humanities center and the stanford institute for creativity and the arts sica present cathy horyn fashion critic for the new york times in conversation with nancy troy chair of art and art history at stanford and author of couture culture a study in modern art and fashion cathy horyn is at stanford as the arts critic in residence for 2010 11 about the speaker cathy horyn has been the fashion critic of the new york times since 1999 she has a blog on the runway and she also covers the industry for the new york times magazine prior to joining the times she was a contributing editor at vanity fair where she wrote profiles of many entertainers and also contributed articles about the fashion and music industries she has also written for vogue harper's bazaar and a number of european publications from 1990 to 1994 she was the fashion reporter for the washington post she began her career in 1980 at the virginian pilot in norfolk virginia a native of coshocton ohio she graduated from barnard college in new york city and has a master's degree in journalism from northwestern university about the lecture series arts critics in residence engages with one of the most essential and currently imperiled arenas of arts criticism journalistic daily and weekly writing for the public it brings leading arts critics to campus to enter into public conversations with art practitioners humanistic scholars and students interested in the arts the arts critics series is jointly presented by the humanities center and sica stanford humanities center website jonathan poto sica photographer 2009 2010 home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a